name: Riley County Health Department
tweet: 12/8/21 COVID-19 Update 106 new cases 6.87% 2-week positive rate  “I highly encourage parents to get their kids vaccinated,” said Local Health Officer Julie Gibbs.  More at:  https://t.co/wDLEJDEUUM  https://t.co/HngVjs6EAX

name: Riley County Health Department
tweet: A total of 315 kids were vaccinated at the COVID-19 clinic this weekend! Santa stopped by to make the process a little less scary and spread holiday cheer. We're so grateful to all of the amazing staff and volunteers whose dedication makes the vaccine clinics possible.  https://t.co/a2cQCaOUs3

name: Riley County Health Department
tweet: Starting this week, the take-home COVID-19 saliva test kits formerly provided by KDHE and distributed at the Health Department will no longer be available. You can still get a free COVID-19 test at the Health Department by calling our Screening Line at (785) 323-6400.  https://t.co/NzUEKKlQT8

name: Riley County Health Department
tweet: 12/1/2021 COVID update A 69-year-old unvaccinated male died on 11/25 after testing positive for COVID-19 on 11/24.  Riley County has identified 57 new COVID-19 cases and 73 additional recoveries. More at:  https://t.co/XYCeNv7Ast  https://t.co/1EoTukFADg

name: Riley County Health Department
tweet: Join Riley County Health Department Director Julie Gibbs, Ascension Via Christi Hospital President Bob Copple and Riley County Health Department Clinic Supervisor Aryn Price, Ph.D., today at 4:30 PM for an update on COVID-19.  https://t.co/Rbzo6G4qyU
